Annamarie is a third-year student at Harvard Law School. She graduated from the University of Rochester in 2018, where she studied both Business and Vocal Performance. She completed her first year of law school at Indiana University Maurer School of Law, after which she transferred to Harvard. She hopes to use her law degree to increase the participation of minority groups (particularly women and the LGBTQ+ community) in government/public policy spaces.
